{
  "text": "Recently, in this direction some research had been done. In [CITATION_1] Christiane Lemieux showed that a negative dependence property of RQMC points ensures that the variance of the corresponding RQMC estimator for functions f that are monotone with respect to each variable is never larger than the variance of the corresponding MC estimator µ MC f . She also proved that a different negative dependence property yields that the variance of the RQMC estimator for an arbitrary bounded quasi-monotone f is never larger than the variance of µ MC f . Those negative dependence properties rely solely on the marginals and the bivariate copulas of the RQMC points (i.e., on the distribution of single points and on the common distribution of pairs of points). Related results can be found in [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
